main event: An official moonwatch report recorded a sighting of a satellite appearing object in Terre Haute, Indiana on January 28, 1961.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on January 28, 1961, at 10:20 AM.,The observation lasted for 1-2 minutes.,The object was suspected to be a satellite, possibly an aircraft, but not a balloon or astronomical object.,The report noted that all known data was not available.,The registered team leader for the observation was from Terre Haute, Indiana.
sighted object: object suspected to be a satellite
witness description: moonwatch team from Terre Haute, Indiana
